Coturnices (he says) when they come to these places travel without guides : but when they go away set out with the Lingulaea. the Otus, and the Matrix as their guides. and also with the Cychramus‚ by which they are moreover summoned back at night. And when the fowlers have heard its cry, they know the birds' departure is at hand.
